  <body>
    <Header />
    <main>
      <h1>Best Foot Rest for Under Desk 2026</h1>
      <div class="meta">Updated June 2026 · Evaluated 7+ models</div>

      <nav class="toc" aria-label="Table of contents">
        <h2>Table of Contents</h2>
        <ol>
          <li><a href="#how-we-evaluated">How We Evaluated</a></li>
          <li><a href="#ranking-methodology">Ranking Methodology</a></li>
          <li><a href="#quick-comparison">Quick Comparison</a></li>
          <li><a href="#best-overall">Best Overall</a></li>
          <li><a href="#best-budget">Best Budget</a></li>
          <li><a href="#buying-guide">Buying Guide</a></li>
          <li><a href="#faq">FAQ</a></li>
        </ol>
      </nav>

      <p>Sitting for eight hours with your feet dangling or pressed flat on the floor is a recipe for lower back pain, swollen ankles, and poor circulation. A footrest is the cheapest ergonomic upgrade you can make after a good chair, and for shorter users it is non-optional — if your chair is at correct desk height but your feet do not reach the floor, you are loading your spine with every minute of dangling. We evaluated seven under-desk footrests based on their specifications and design features to find which ones actually improve comfort versus just occupying floor space.</p>

      <h2 id="how-we-evaluated">How We Evaluated</h2>
      <p>We evaluated 7 under-desk footrest models based on product documentation, specifications, feature analysis, and pricing comparison. Our evaluation methodology follows the <a href="/how-we-test/">ToolStep review protocol</a>, analyzing product documentation, specifications, features, and pricing. Each product was assessed across identical criteria to ensure fair comparison.</p>
      <p>We evaluated each product on four criteria: Performance (30%), Build Quality (25%), Value (20%), and Ease of Use (25%). Scores were compiled from specification analysis and feature evaluation, not marketing claims. For adjustability we assessed height range and tilt specifications based on manufacturer documentation. For slip resistance we evaluated base material specifications and surface compatibility claims across carpet and hard floor surfaces. For comfort we assessed cushion material, foam density specifications, and ergonomic design features.</p>

      <h2 id="ranking-methodology">Ranking Methodology</h2>
      <p>Our rankings are based on weighted scoring across four dimensions:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Performance (30%)</strong> — Ergonomic benefit and circulation improvement</li>
        <li><strong>Build Quality (25%)</strong> — Frame rigidity, cushion durability, and hinge strength</li>
        <li><strong>Value (20%)</strong> — Price-to-performance ratio compared to alternatives</li>
        <li><strong>Ease of Use (25%)</strong> — Adjustability range, slip resistance, and setup</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="quick-comparison">Quick Comparison</h2>
