            <td>$12</td>
            <td>4.0/5</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2 id="best-overall">Best Overall: HUANUO Adjustable Foot Rest</h2>
      <p>The HUANUO won because it was the only rest in our comparison that offered genuine height and tilt adjustability at a reasonable price, which is the entire point of a footrest. Fixed-height rests force you to adapt to them; the HUANUO adapts to you. The three height levels (4.7, 5.7, and 6.7 inches) cover the full range needed for users between 5'4" and 6'0", and the 30-degree tilt adjustment lets each user dial in a neutral ankle angle.</p>
      <p>The memory foam top layer is what makes this comfortable for full workdays rather than just the first hour. Cheaper foam rests compress flat within a few hours and offer no cushioning by afternoon. According to the manufacturer, the HUANUO's high-density memory foam is designed to retain its shape over extended use, and the textured bumps on the underside of the cushion cover (flipped for use) provide a gentle foot-massage effect that stimulates circulation when you rock your feet.</p>
      <p>The non-slip base is designed to hold firm on both carpet and hardwood surfaces, resisting the forward sliding that cheaper plastic rests exhibit under normal foot pressure. The adjustment mechanism is tool-free and locks positively into each height, with no wobble once set. The one downside is the footprint: at 17 by 10 inches it is larger than some competitors, so check your under-desk clearance if you share the space with a PC tower or cable box.</p>

      <div class="product-box">
        <h2>HUANUO Adjustable Foot Rest</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>3 height levels from 4.7" to 6.7"</strong> — covers full range for 5'4" to 6'0" users</li>
          <li><strong>30-degree tilt angle adjustment</strong> — dial in neutral ankle position</li>
          <li><strong>Textured surface for foot massage</strong> — stimulates circulation when rocking</li>
